  "texts": [
    "One such method is the DC chopper system, where excess energy stored in the DC link is dumped during voltage sags to avoid overvoltage and maintain power transfer [25].",
    "This has also been applied to grid-side converter control, allowing the wind turbine to supply reactive power to the grid during voltage dips, thus improving grid stability and voltage restoration [9,13].",
    "This method also enhances the turbine's ability to meet grid code requirements.",
    "Additional developments include crowbar protection combined with enhanced converter control and Model Predictive Control (MPC), which refine LVRT capabilities by minimizing rotor speed oscillations and improving system performance during faults [26,27].",
    "Together, these techniques increase the reliability and robustness of DFIG wind turbines, making them more responsive to grid fluctuations."
  ],
